<br>
Blade of Advanced Tactics<br>
14/20 +10 str, +20 dex, +75 hp, +10 MR, +10 FR, +10 CR<br>
Effect:Blessing of Zek(worn, +75 atk, +20 ac, +20 dex)<br>
<br>
Blade of Superior Strategy<br>
12/18 +10 str, +20 sta, +10 agi, +75 hp, +10 MR         +10 DR, +10 PR<br>
Effect:Fury of Zek(combat,125 DD(MR) , +500 hate)<br>
<br>
Quest requirements<br>
Blade of Tactics(RoK epic)<br>
Blade of Strategy(RoK epic)<br>
Spirit Stone of Zek(Rallos Zek drop)<br>
Blood of Storms(Karana drop)<br>
Hammer of Raging Flame(Solusek Ro drop)<br>
Level 60<br>
Blade Molds(read below)<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
~Quest~<br>
So you have obtained the Blade of Strategy and the Blade of Tactics? You must show me them before I continue our conversation!<br>
(give NPC old epics, he hands them back)<br>
<br>
So you have obtained them! Then you are a true Warlord! Then perhaps I have some knowledge that would interest you. I have found a way to release the true power of these blades! For many ages, the true power of them have been held back by the gods. However, I know how you can break this seal and return them to their true state. <br>
(NPC gives you 2 nodrop molds, none if not level 60, and the conversation ends here)<br>
<br>
In order to release the true power of the Blade of Strategy and Blade of Tactics, you must place them inside the mold, and then into a forge. Hammer into the molds a [stone blessed by Zek himself] ,using a[hammer enchanted by a fiery essence],and cool the new blades using [the purest water] in existance.<br>
<br>
What stone blessed by Zek himself?<br>
<br>
I have read from ancient tomes of knowledge that Rallos Zek himself holds an ore of immense power. It is within this ore that he holds the true power of the blades. Go and slay him, and prove you are the true Warlord of the realms by restoring your blades!<br>
(RZ follows can obtain it through a miniquest, it's written in the next section)<br>
<br>
What hammer enchanted by a fiery essence?<br>
<br>
Ah, so you wish to know how to obtain the hammer to forge your new blades? I do not know the exact location of this hammer myself. Rumour has it that the Burning Prince was the last to wield it, however this was ages ago.<br>
<br>
What is the purest water?<br>
<br>
Ah, the purest water of course is the blood of The Rainkeeper! I do not believe he will give this willingly.. but perhaps it is worth a try to talk to him.<br>
(Karana worshippers can obtain it through a miniquest given by Karana himself, others must slay him)<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
~Side Quests~<br>
You say, Rallos Zek, I seek the stone the holds your essence!<br>
<br>
Rallos Zek Says, So you wish to have the stone do you mortal? Well you can not have it! Now leave me be, I have [important matters] to attend to!<br>
<br>
What important matters?<br>
<br>
Rallos Zek says, Those blasted nature lovers are trying to end my rule! I require for you to bring back the Heart of Karana or Golden Braid of Tunare's hair! Now begone mortal!<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
I wish for some of your blood Karana<br>
<br>
Karana says, Why do you need this blood, young mortal?<br>
<br>
To release the powers of the Blades of Tactics and Strategy kind Rainkeeper<br>
<br>
Karana says, Ah, I see! A true Warlord has joined my side! This is truely a wonderful day indeed. I will happily give you a simple of my blood, however you must bring me the Brain of Cazic-Thule to prove yourself. Knowing his thoughts would help me better prepare us for the wars that are to come. Return to me and I shall reward you with a vile of my blood Warlord!<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
This would give us better epics with upgraded effects, but not make the quest very easy to balance it.<br>
The drops from the 3 PoP gods should be 75% chance so you can't get a new one EVERY respawn, which would also cause an issue. All pieces would be nodrop/no stats.<br>
<br>
The hate proc would have an increased DD and become MR based. <br>
<br>
You could also go back and quest your epics over again (if you had the time/plat) to wield both red epics.<br>
<br>
I would also like the upgraded epics to have red/blue flames instead of the lightsaber graphic. Red/blue flames would just look neat=P<br>
<br>
Feedback welcomed.<br>
